docs.abstract: The president’s most significant achievement on trade — a revised deal with Canada and Mexico — is imperiled amid Democratic and Republican concerns.
docs.snippet: The president’s most significant achievement on trade — a revised deal with Canada and Mexico — is imperiled amid Democratic and Republican concerns.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump lauded his new trade agreement with Canada and Mexico in his State of the Union address on Tuesday and urged Congress to pass the revised pact. The deal, he argued, will help American farmers and workers and ensure “that more cars are proudly stamped with the four beautiful words: Made in the U.S.A.”

headline.main: Trump Loves the New Nafta. Congress Doesn’t.
headline.print_headline: New Nafta Deal Faces Headwinds in Congress

docs.lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — In his first major public address since the grounding of the 737 Max fleet, Boeing’s chief executive faced questions about the company’s credibility and its safety procedures following two fatal crashes involving the brand-new jet.

headline.main: Boeing Chief Seeks to Reassure Shareholders on Safety of 737 Max Jets
headline.print_headline: Boeing Chief Seeks to Reassure Shareholders on 737 Max

docs.abstract: While the I.R.S. has said it expects refunds to be issued on schedule, the agency is going to take a while to return to normal after the government shutdown.

docs.lead_paragraph: Tax preparers, bracing for a tricky filing season, are advising taxpayers to file returns as they usually do, but to be prepared for possible delays if they are due refunds.

docs.abstract: The British company said it would no longer use the Chinese telecommunications giant’s equipment in some parts of its network in Europe because of political factors.
docs.snippet: The British company said it would no longer use the Chinese telecommunications giant’s equipment in some parts of its network in Europe because of political factors.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — The Chinese telecommunications giant Huawei was dealt another blow on Friday when one of the world’s largest wireless carriers suspended its purchases from the company in Europe over security concerns about its ties to the Chinese government.

headline.main: Vodafone, One of World’s Largest Cell Carriers, Halts Buying of Huawei Gear
headline.print_headline: Huawei Dealt Another Blow As Cell Carrier  Halts Purchases

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Trade Commission is in the advanced stages of its investigation into whether Facebook violated privacy rules and is expected to seek large fines from the company, according to two people familiar with the inquiry.

headline.main: F.T.C. Is Said to Be Considering Large Facebook Fines
headline.print_headline: F.T.C. Is Said To Consider Hefty Fines For Facebook

docs.abstract: The cold war between Facebook and Apple over data use and privacy is heating up. How far should Mr. Cook take it?
docs.snippet: The cold war between Facebook and Apple over data use and privacy is heating up. How far should Mr. Cook take it?
docs.lead_paragraph: It’s nowhere in his job description, but Tim Cook, Apple’s chief executive, has recently taken a moonlight gig as Facebook’s privacy watchdog.

headline.main: Maybe Only Tim Cook Can Fix Facebook’s Privacy Problem
headline.print_headline: Maybe Only Apple’s C.E.O. Can Protect Facebook Users

docs.abstract: The company is compensating for slowing growth in e-commerce by expanding its fast-moving, highly profitable cloud and advertising businesses.
docs.snippet: The company is compensating for slowing growth in e-commerce by expanding its fast-moving, highly profitable cloud and advertising businesses.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Amazon held off stiffer competition for online shoppers during the holiday season, once again increasing its sales. But the company said on Thursday that growth slowed from its usual breakneck pace — and it came at a cost, with the company spending far more on shipping to win customers.

headline.main: Amazon’s Sales Growth Slows, Even as Cloud Business Stays Hot
headline.print_headline: Amazon’s Sales Growth Slows, But Cloud Unit Bolsters Profits

docs.abstract: More than 100,000 women are resolving claims against companies that made pelvic mesh products to treat urinary problems. Lawyers have found ways to take big chunks of their payouts.
docs.snippet: More than 100,000 women are resolving claims against companies that made pelvic mesh products to treat urinary problems. Lawyers have found ways to take big chunks of their payouts.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Sherise Grant filed a claim against the manufacturer of her pelvic mesh implant, she hoped to use the money from a settlement to pay for its removal.

headline.main: As Pelvic Mesh Settlements Near $8 Billion, Women Question Lawyers’ Fees
headline.print_headline: For Women, It Was Painful.  For Lawyers, It Was Profitable.
